rovals%20for%20his%20nominees%20for%20posts%20in%20his%20administration%20-%20something%20he%20had%20struggled%20with%20during%20his%20first%20term%20back%20in%202017%20when%20internal%20resistance%20within%20the%20Republican%20Party%20was%20significantly%20higher.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Does%20US%20Congress%20Work%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Congress%20has%20a%20total%20of%20535%20members%2C%20including%20100%20representatives%20in%20the%20Senate%20and%20435%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives.%20Each%20of%20the%2050%20states%20in%20the%20US%20sends%20two%20Senators%20to%20the%20US%20Senate.%20However%2C%20the%20state's%20representation%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%20is%20based%20on%20its%20population.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20smaller%20state%20like%20Vermont%20has%20one%20representative%20while%20large%20states%20like%20California%20have%2053%20representatives%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20term%20of%20members%20of%20the%20House%20of%20Representatives%20is%20two%20years%20and%20all%20435%20seats%20are%20considered%20for%20reelection%20every%20even%20year.%20This%20marks%20a%20stark%20contrast%20with%20the%20Senate%2C%20the%20upper%20chamber%20of%20Congress%2C%20where%20senators%20serve%20six-year%20terms.%20Elections%20to%20the%20Senate%20are%20staggered%20over%20even%20years%20so%20that%20only%20about%201%2F3%20of%20the%20Senate%20is%20up%20for%20reelection%20during%20any%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20single-party%20control%20of%20Congress%2C%20which%20was%20once%20common%2C%20has%20become%20rare%20and%20short%20over%20the%20past%20few%20decades%2C%20with%20the%20party%20in%20power%20losing%20seats%20when%20midterm%20congressional%20elections%20are%20held%20every%20two%20years.%20Both%20former%20President%20Trump%20and%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20enjoyed%20%26quot%3Btrifectas%26quot%3B%20for%20their%20first%20two%20years%20in%20the%20White%20House%2C%20but%20the%20dynamics%20changed%20following%20midterm%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EDoes%20'Trifecta'%20Guarantee%20Absolute%20Power%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20'trifecta'%20is%20no%20guarantee%20against%20political%20infighting.%20Despite%20the%20Biden%20administration%20having%20%26quot%3Btrifecta%26quot%3B%20from%202021%20to%202023%2C%20internal%20dissent%20stymied%20certain%20policy%20priorities%2C%20with%20figures%20like%20Arizona's%20independent%20Senator%20Kyrsten%20Sinema%20resisting%20party%20orthodoxy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20major%20obstacle%20in%20the%20way%20of%20total%20control%20by%20either%20party%20is%20that%20it%20requires%20a%20three-fifths%20majority%20-%20or%2060%20votes%20out%20of%20100%20-%20to%20pass%20bills%20in%20the%20Senate.%20Therefore%2C%20to%20bypass%20the%20filibuster%20or%20the%20tradition%20of%20unlimited%20debate%2C%20a%20party%20needs%20a%20healthy%20majority%20in%20the%20Senate.%20Hence%2C%20should%20a%20party%20have%20a%20simple%20majority%20in%20the%20Senate%2C%20it%20needs%20to%20reach%20across%20the%20aisle%20to%20get%20a%20bill%20passed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20a%20report%20in%20the%20New%20York%20Times%2C%20Mr%20Trump%20is%20likely%20to%20get%20a%20healthy%20majority%20in%20the%20Senate%20this%20time%20around.%20However%2C%20despite%20that%2C%20he%20may%20not%20have%20the%20magic%2060%20seats%20that%20would%20allow%20him%20to%20overcome%20opposition%20attempts%20to%20delay%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20there%20are%20already%20signs%20that%20Donald%20Trump%20may%20not%20have%20his%20way%20at%20all%20times%2C%20with%20his%20party%20selecting%20John%20Thune%20as%20the%20Senate%20majority%20leader%20despite%20Rick%20Scott%20being%20reportedly%20favoured%20for%20the%20post%20by%20by%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20Mr%20Trump%20did%20not%20officially%20endorse%20Scott%2C%20the%20American%20media%20is%20seeing%20Mr%20Thune's%20selection%20as%20a%20sign%20that%20some%20Republican%20lawmakers%20are%20asserting%20their%20independence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20The%20%26quot%3BTrifecta%26quot%3B%20Can%20Benefit%20Trump%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20said%2C%20if%20managed%20astutely%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Btrifecta%26quot%3B%20can%20open%20the%20way%20for%20the%20possibility%20of%20significant%20legislative%20initiatives.%20A%20majority%20in%20both%20chambers%20of%20Congress%20may%20give%20Mr%20Trump%20an%20advantage%20in%20pushing%20through%20his%20right-wing%20agenda%20and%20big%20poll%20promises%20like%20the%20largest%20deportation%20of%20migrants%20in%20history%2C%20sweeping%20tariffs%20on%20foreign%20imports%2C%20and%20the%20rolling%20back%20of%20environmental%20protections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20follow%2C%20no%20index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F11%2F13%2Fus%2Felections%2Frepublican-house-trifecta.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENYT%3C%2Fa%3E%20report%2C%20using%20legislation%20to%20achieve%20these%20goals%20will%20make%20them%20much%20harder%20to%20overturn%20in%20the%20courts%2C%20especially%20with%20the%20judicial%20landscape%20also%20in%20Mr%20Trump's%20favour.%20In%20his%20first%20term%2C%20the%20former%20President%20was%20able%20to%20put%20three%20conservatives%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20-%20cementing%20a%20two-thirds%20majority%20for%20years%20to%20come.%20He%20also%20named%20more%20than%20four%20dozen%20judges%20to%20the%20federal%20appeals%20courts%2C%20bending%20several%20circuits%20to%20a%20more%20conservative%20bent.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1731582300000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-11%2Fss6rc438_us-congress-afp_625x300_14_November_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdonald-trump-wins-big-as-republicans-bag-trifecta-of-victories-how-it-helps-him-7017743%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%20is%20likely%20to%20get%20a%20healthy%20majority%20in%20the%20Senate%20this%20time%20ar