d%20by%20how%20investors%20expect%20Fed%20policy%20to%20affect%20the%20broader%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFed%20officials%20have%20lowered%20the%20federal%20funds%20rate%20twice%20so%20far%20this%20year%2C%20and%20they're%20expected%20to%20continue%20lowering%20it%20at%20future%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22When%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%20Down%3F%5C%22%3EWhen%20Will%20Mortgage%20Rates%20Go%20Down%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20major%20forecasts%20expect%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwill-mortgage-rates-go-down-this-year%5C%22%3Emortgage%20rates%20to%20go%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20they%20may%20not%20drop%20a%20lot%20in%20the%20near%20term.%20We%20should%20see%20rates%20fall%20in%202025.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMortgage%20rates%20started%20ticking%20up%20from%20historic%20lows%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202021%20and%20increased%20dramatically%20in%202022%20and%20throughout%20most%20of%202023.%20But%20now%20that%20inflation%20has%20decelerated%20and%20the%20Fed%20has%20started%20cutting%20rates%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20have%20trended%20down%20compared%20to%20where%20they%20were%20a%20year%20ago.%20In%20the%20last%2012%20months%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finflation-october-cpi-consumer-price-index-federal-reserve-interest-rates-2024-11%5C%22%3Econsumer%20price%20index%20rose%20by%202.6%25%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20a%20significant%20slowdown%20compared%20to%20when%20it%20peaked%20at%209.1%25%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20much%20rates%20go%20down%20depends%20on%20how%20the%20economy%20evolves.%20If%20economic%20conditions%20remain%20stable%2C%20mortgage%20rates%20may%20not%20fall%20as%20much.%20But%20if%20the%20labor%20market%20weakens%20and%20the%20Fed%20has%20to%20cut%20rates%20more%20aggressively%2C%20we%20could%20see%20rates%20drop%20substantially.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERates%20are%20unlikely%20to%20drop%20back%20down%20to%20the%20historic%20lows%20of%202020%20and%202021%2C%20when%2030-year%20fixed%20rates%20fell%20below%203%25.%20But%20we%20could%20see%20them%20settle%20in%20the%205%25%20range%20in%20the%20next%20few%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22Will%20Home%20Prices%20Drop%20in%202024%3F%5C%22%3EWill%20Home%20Prices%20Drop%20in%202024%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20aren't%20likely%20to%20see%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fhome-prices-drop%5C%22%3Ehome%20prices%20drop%3C%2Fa%3E%20anytime%20soon%20thanks%20to%20extremely%20limited%20supply.%20In%20fact%2C%20they'll%20likely%20rise%20this%20year%20as%20mortgage%20rates%20drop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fanniemae.com%2Fmedia%2F53421%2Fdisplay%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFannie%20Mae%20researchers%3C%2Fa%3E%20expect%20prices%20to%20increase%205.8%25%20in%202024%2C%20while%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mba.org%2Fnews-and-research%2Fforecasts-and-commentary%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMortgage%20Bankers%20Association%3C%2Fa%3E%20expects%20a%203.8%25%20increase%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELower%20mortgage%20rates%20will%20bring%20more%20buyers%20onto%20the%20market%2C%20putting%20upward%20pressure%20on%20prices.%20But%20prices%20aren't%20expected%20to%20increase%20as%20much%20as%20they%20have%20in%20recent%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-label%3D%5C%22How%20to%20Choose%20a%20Mortgage%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20Choose%20a%20Mortgage%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20options%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20finding%20the%20right%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Ftypes-of-mortgage-loans%5C%22%3Etype%20of%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20you.%20First%2C%20you'll%20need%20to%20decide%20if%20you%20want%20a%20fixed-rate%20mortgage%20or%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fadjustable-rate-mortgage%5C%22%3Eadjustable-rate%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Fwhat-is-fixed-rate-mortgage%5C%22%3EFixed-rate%20mortgages%3C%2Fa%3E%20lock%20in%20your%20rate%20for%20the%20entire%20life%20of%20your%20loan.%20Adjustable-rate%20mortgages%20lock%20in%20your%20rate%20for%20the%20first%20few%20years%2C%20then%20your%20rate%20can%20go%20up%20or%20down%20periodically%20based%20on%20market%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EFixed-Rate%20vs.%20Adjustable-Rate%20Mortgage%20Pros%20and%20Cons%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20do%20you%20choose%20between%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Ffixed-rate-mortgage-vs-adjustable-rate-mortgage%5C%22%3Efixed-rate%20vs.%20adjustable-rate%20mortgage%3C%2Fa%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EARMs%20often%20(but%20not%20always)%20start%20with%20lower%20rates%20than%20fixed-rate%20mortgages%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fmortgages%2Farm-rates-today%5C%22%3EARM%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%20change%20once%20your%20fixed-rate%20introductory%20period%20is%20over.%20If%20you%20plan%20on%20moving%20or%20refinancing%20before%20the%20rate%20adjusts%2C%20an%20ARM%20could%20be%20a%20good%20deal.%20But%20keep%20in%20mind%20that%20a%20change%20in%20circumstances%20could%20prevent%20you%20from%20doing%20these%20things%2C%20so%20it's%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20think%20about%20whether%20your%20budget%20could%20handle%20a%20higher%20monthly%20payment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFixed-rate%20mortgages%20are%20a%20good%20choice%20for%20borrowers%20who%20want%20stability%2C%20since%20your%20monthly%20principal%20and%20interest%20payments%20won't%20change%20throughout%20the%20life%20of%20the%20loan%20(though%20your%20mortgage%20payment%20could%20increase%20if%20your%20taxes%20or%20insurance%20go%20up).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20exchange%20for%20this