20to%20go%20after%20other%20targets%20in%20depth%2C%20experts%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20Iranian%20ballistic%20missiles%2C%20Russia%20has%20a%20flexibility%20that%20could%20be%20a%20big%20problem%20for%20Ukraine.%20It%20can%20hammer%20front-line%20positions%20with%20cheap%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-ballistic-missiles-iran-greater-flexibility-ukraine-us-warns-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIranian%20weapons%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20reserving%20its%20more%20expensive%20weapons%20for%20other%20targets%20at%20depth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20cost-benefit%20perspective%2C%20low-value%20Ukrainian%20targets%20on%20the%20front%20lines%20aren't%20ideal%20for%20expensive%2C%20sophisticated%20precision-guided%20missiles%2C%20stockpiles%20that%20are%20consistently%20strained%20as%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20delivery%20of%20cheaper%20Iranian%20missiles%20creates%20new%20options.%20%26quot%3BRussia's%20focus%20is%20probably%20going%20to%20be%20on%20using%20those%20to%20do%20sort%20of%20the%20short%20tactical%20battlefield%20targets%2C%26quot%3B%20Timothy%20Wright%2C%20a%20missile%20technology%20expert%20at%20the%20International%20Institute%20for%20Strategic%20Studies%20(IISS)%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226af626de-33ac-451c-95fe-99caef61c2d1%5C%22%3ENew%20missiles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20European%20defense%20officials%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Faerospace-defense%2Firan-deliver-hundreds-ballistic-missiles-russia-soon-intel-sources-say-2024-08-09%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20August%20that%20they%20expected%20Iran%20to%20deliver%20hundreds%20of%20Fath-360%20short-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20to%20Russia%2C%20as%20well%20as%20some%20Ababil%20close-range%20ballistic%20missiles.%20The%20Pentagon%20confirmed%20the%20Fath-360%20delivery%20in%20September.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFath-360s%2C%20Pentagon%20Press%20Secretary%20Air%20Force%20Maj.%20Gen.%20Pat%20Ryder%20said%2C%20are%20believed%20to%20have%20a%20range%20of%20about%2075%20miles.%20Ababils%20have%20a%20range%20of%20around%2053%20miles%2C%20according%20to%20the%20IISS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20clear%20if%20Russia%20has%20used%20either%20system%20yet.%20Reuters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Firan-withheld-launchers-missiles-sent-russia-sources-say-2024-09-21%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20September%20that%20Iran%20did%20not%20include%20launchers%20for%20the%20Fath-360%20missiles%20in%20the%20deliveries%2C%20so%20it%20may%20not%20have%20the%20capacity%20to%20fire%20them%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20presumably%20they%20intend%20to%20use%20them.%20Wright%20said%20that%20Russia's%20plan%20is%20probably%20to%20%26quot%3Bget%20the%20Iranian%20stuff%20on%20board%20so%20they%20can%20go%20after%20stuff%20within%20the%20immediate%20periphery%20of%20the%20front%20lines.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFabian%20Hofffman%2C%20a%20doctoral%20research%20fellow%20with%20the%20Oslo%20Nuclear%20Project%2C%20told%20BI%20%26quot%3BIranian%20missiles%2C%20by%20lack%20of%20their%20own%20range%2C%20are%20restricted%20to%20front-line%20targets%20for%20sure.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20the%20Iranian%20missiles%20%26quot%3Ballow%20Russia%20to%20put%20even%20more%20pressure%20on%20front-line%20targets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22de3eb5c7-6c62-405d-80d4-15adcb1a8937%5C%22%3EFreeing%20up%20Russian%20missiles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERyder%2C%20the%20Pentagon%20spokesman%2C%20said%20in%20September%20that%20the%20Iranian%20missiles%20%26quot%3Bwould%20enable%20Russia%20to%20employ%20this%20capability%20while%20preserving%20its%20longer-range%20capabilities%20for%20use%20throughout%20the%20battlefield%2C%20thus%20deepening%20Russia's%20arsenal.%26quot%3B%20Russia%20could%20focus%20on%20striking%20the%20targets%20it's%20already%20been%20striking%2C%20like%20civilian%20targets%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20targets%20for%20Russian%20missiles%20could%20be%20high-value%20Ukrainian%20systems%20in%20the%20rear.%20It%20isn't%20clear%20exactly%20to%20what%20extent%20Iran's%20ballistic%20missiles%20will%20free%20up%20other%20Russian%20precision%20munitions%20for%20other%20targets%2C%20but%20Hoffman%20said%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20overall%20volume%20is%20going%20to%20increase.%26quot%3B%20That%20gives%20Russia%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Russian%20Iskander%20missile%20launcher%20is%20seen%20in%20August%202022%20outside%20Moscow.%20These%20missiles%20were%20destroyed%20in%20a%20Ukrainian%20drone%20attack%20overnight.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66eadc77cfb7f307e5729a1e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222363%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Russian%20Iskander%20missile%20launcher.%3Cp%3EPhoto%20by%20Contributor%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFabian%20Hinz%2C%20an%20IISS%20missile%20expert%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.iiss.org%2Fonline-analysis%2Fmissile-dialogue-initiative%2F2024%2F09%2Firanian-missile-deliveries-to-russia-escalating-military-cooperation-in-ukraine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20September%20analysis%20that%20using%20shorter-range%20Iranian%20missiles%20could%20free%20up%20Russia's%20Iskander%20missiles%2C%20which%20have%20a%20longer%20range%2C%20%26quot%3Bfor%20additional%20attacks%20against%20targets%20in%20Ukraine's%20depth.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bwhile%20these%20Iranian%20missiles%20may%20not%20introduce%20a%20new%20capability%20to%20Russia's%20war%20effort%2C%20they%20will%20offer%20increased%20flexibility%20and%2C%20most%20importantly%2C%20additional%20quantity.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22eda11e7d-e6a6-4beb-851a-f258b8181bfe%5C%22%3ERussia-Iran%20ties%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERus