20not%20that%20they%20don't%20%3Cem%3Ewant%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20learn%3B%20it's%20that%20nobody's%20teaching%20them.%20In%20many%20pockets%20of%20corporate%20America%2C%20on-the-job%20training%20mostly%20amounts%20to%20%26quot%3Bfigure%20it%20out.%26quot%3B%20Workers%20are%20struggling%20to%20get%20a%20handle%20on%20their%20jobs%2C%20and%20this%20failure%20falls%20on%20everyone%20%E2%80%94%20companies%2C%20managers%2C%20human-resources%20departments%2C%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20workers%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20don't%20need%20to%20look%20far%20to%20find%20evidence%20that%20people%20don't%20feel%20ready%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20work.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-workers-are-lazy-lack-soft-skills-managers-say-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebosses%20complain%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20don't%20know%20what%20they're%20doing%20and%20are%20lazy.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-lazy-hiring-jobs-careers-hr-training-pandemic-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHR%20professionals%20and%20Gen%20Z%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20argue%20that%20young%20people%20want%20to%20be%20successful%20in%20the%20workforce%2C%20but%20they%20simply%20aren't%20given%20the%20tools%20to%20do%20it.%20In%20a%20survey%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.adobe.com%2Fen%2Fpublish%2F2023%2F09%2F27%2Fadobe-future-workforce-study-what-us-employers-need-know-about-gen-z-workplace%23%3A~%3Atext%3DGen%2520Z%2520is%2520hungry%2520for%2520mentorship%2520and%2520development%26amp%3Btext%3DGen%2520Z%2520is%2520eager%2520for%2Cpercent)%2520reported%2520having%2520a%2520mentor.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoftware%20company%20Adobe%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2083%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20respondents%20said%20having%20a%20mentor%20at%20work%20was%20crucial%20to%20their%20career%2C%20but%20only%20half%20said%20they%20had%20a%20mentor.%20It's%20not%20just%20young%20workers%20who%20are%20facing%20a%20training%20problem%3B%20it's%20everybody.%20For%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2F394373%2Findicator-employee-engagement.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup's%20employee-engagement%20indicator%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20analyzes%20employee%20perspectives%20using%20random%20samples%20of%20working%20adults%2C%20less%20than%20half%20of%20US%20employees%20said%20they%20knew%20what's%20expected%20of%20them%20at%20work.%20This%20is%20a%20costly%20problem%2C%20too%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fworkplace%2F393497%2Fworld-trillion-workplace-problem.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20employees%20who%20weren't%20engaged%20cost%20%248.8%20trillion%20in%20lost%20productivity%20worldwide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20figuring%20out%20the%20day-to-day%20basics%20of%20the%20job%20is%20a%20challenge.%20The%20pandemic-driven%20upheaval%20of%20the%20past%20several%20years%20led%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgreat-resignation-still-going-layoffs-low-job-openings-quits-high-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20amounts%20of%3C%2Fa%3E%20job-hopping%2C%20organizational%20brain%20drain%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Floyalty-employee-employer-job-security-broken-work-companies-bosses-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edecline%20in%20loyalty%3C%2Fa%3E%20among%20employers%20and%20employees.%20The%20chaos%20has%20left%20employers%2C%20managers%2C%20and%20employees%20wondering%20just%20how%20much%20time%20and%20money%20it's%20worth%20investing%20in%20training%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20The%20rise%20of%20remote%20and%20hybrid%20work%20has%20complicated%20the%20situation%20even%20more.%20It's%20tough%20to%20learn%20by%20osmosis%20over%20Slack%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhr-software-tech-companies-employees-productivity-workday-oracle-adp-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20deluge%20of%20HR%20apps%20and%20training%20modules%3C%2Fa%3E%20isn't%20filling%20in%20the%20gaps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20companies%20want%20employees%20to%20'hit%20the%20ground%20running'%20and%20use%20apps%2C%20AI%2C%20and%20training%20videos%20to%20avoid%20disrupting%20another%20employee's%20flow%20or%20for%20the%20lack%20of%20staff%20to%20train%20someone%20new%20or%20help%20someone%20learn%20a%20new%20skill%2C%26quot%3B%20Ana%20Goehner%2C%20a%20career%20strategist%20and%20HR%20professional%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20may%20work%20in%20some%20instances%2C%20but%20in%20others%2C%20instead%20of%20hitting%20the%20ground%20running%2C%20workers%20find%20themselves%20perpetually%20zig-zagging%2C%20unable%20to%20break%20into%20a%20full%20sprint.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20people%20feel%20like%20they're%20not%20equipped%20to%20do%20their%20jobs%20isn't%20a%20new%20phenomenon.%20There's%20been%20a%20long-standing%20decay%20of%20investment%20in%20learning%20and%20training%20by%20employers%20as%20part%20of%20an%20effort%20to%20create%20leaner%20organizations%2C%20said%20Kenneth%20Matos%2C%20the%20director%20of%20market%20insights%20at%20HiBob%2C%20an%20HR-tech%20company.%20If%20you're%20cutting%20costs%2C%20training%20is%20an%20easy%20place%20to%20do%20it.%20That's%20especially%20true%20when%20many%20employers%20use%20the%20internet%20to%20access%20a%20wider%20talent%20pool%20than%20in%20the%20past%2C%20which%20means%20they%20can%20just%20look%20for%20a%20candidate%20who%20already%20knows%20everything%20instead%20of%20having%20to%20teach%20someone.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20plenty%20of%20companies%20have%20been%20axing%20middle%20managers%2C%20the%20people%20who%20would%20have%20previously%20been%20in%20charge%20of%20training%20up%20younger%20or%20newer%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20cut%20away%20the%20people%20who%20are%20the%20link%20between%20big%20strategic%20ideas%20and%20day-to-day%20tactical%20activities%2C%26quot%3B%20Matos%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20you%20end%20up%20with%20a%20scenario%20of%20a%20big%20strategic%20speaker%20talking%20to%20a%20much%20more%20junior%20doer%2C%20and%20they're%20like%2C%20'I%20don't%20know%20how%20this%20translates%20into%20my%20job.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMaking%20matters%20worse%2C%20in%20many%20workplaces%2C%20training%20and%20mentoring%20are%20treated%20as%20an%20extra%2C%20rather%20than%20an%20integral%20part%20of%20the%20job%2C%20if%20they're%20noticed%20at%20all.%20In%20your%20performance%20review%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20spent%2010%20minutes%20explaining%20something%20to%20the%20new%20guy%20he%20was%20too%20afraid%20to%20ask%20his%20boss%20about%26quot%3B%20doesn't%20rate%20very%20highly.%20As%20workers%20and%20managers%20are%20increasingly%20overextended%2C%20these%20types%20of%20unmeasured%2C%20softer%20activities%20can%20fall%20by%20the%20wayside.%20This%20creates%20a%20conflicting%20web%20of%20incentives.%20It%20may%20be%20better%2C%20organizationally%2C%20for%20a%20manager%20or%20experienced%20employee%20to%20spend%20time%20teaching%20everyone%20on%20their%20team%20to%20complete%20a%20complex%20task%20so%20that%20a%20team's%20performance%20is%20better%20overall%2C%20but%20if%20they%20have%20an%20individual%20quota%20to%20meet%2C%20they%20may%20opt%20to%20focus%20on%20doing%20the%20task%20themselves%2C%20even%20though%20it's%20not%20what's%20best%20for%20the%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20end%20up%20with%20this%20really%20weird%20tension%20around%20organizational%20citizenship%20behaviors%20like%20mentoring%20and%20developing%20employees%2C%26quot%3B%20Matos%20said.%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20give%20a%20manager%20a%20lower%20quota%20because%20they%20are%20also%20magnifying%20everybody%20else's%2C%20or%20are%20you%20assuming%20they're%20going%20to%20do%20more%20than%20everybody%20else%2C%20are%20more%20talented%2C%20and%20also%20do%20the%20mentoring%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20in%20the%20middle%20%E2%80%94%20who%20find%20themselves%20in%20between%20the%20big%20bosses%20and%20the%20little%20guys%20%E2%80%94%20are%20going%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20managing%20up%20than%20managing%20down.%20It's%20hard%20to%20tell%20the%20CEO%20that%20you%20can't%20come%20to%20that%20third%20unnecessary%20meeting%20of%20the%20day%20because%20your%20time%20would%20be%20better%20spent%20training%20that%20new%20hire%20on%20logging%20sales%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BManagers%20feel%20so%20caught%20up%2C%20and%20oftentimes%20they%20feel%20pressure%20of%2C%20'OK%2C%20well%20if%20I'm%20going%20to%20disappoint%20someone%2C%20then%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20someone%20junior%20to%20me%20and%20not%20someone%20senior%20to%20me%2C'%26quot%3B%20said%20Ashley%20Herd%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Manager%20Method%2C%20a%20training%20platform%20for%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20managers%20really%20are%20over%20it.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gallup.com%2Fworkplace%2F510326%2Fmanager-squeeze-new-workplace-testing-team-leaders.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGallup%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20in%202023%2C%20managers%20were%20likelier%20than%20nonmanagers%20to%20say%20they're%20disengaged%20at%20work%2C%20burned%20out%2C%20and%20on%20the%20lookout%20for%20a%20new%20job.%20Their%20workers%20have%20been%20given%20more%20responsibilities%2C%20their%20teams%20have%20been%20restructured%2C%20and%20they're%20expected%20to%20accomplish%20everything%20with%20fewer%20resources%2C%20as%20in%2C%20money.%20And%20less%20than%20half%20of%20managers%20said%20they're%20sure%20they%20already%20had%20the%20skills%20needed%20to%20be%20great%20at%20their%20jobs%2C%20meaning%20managers%20weren't%20getting%20taught%20to%20be%20managers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20r%2Fmanagers%20forum%20on%20Reddit%2C%20the%20what-am-I-doing%20sentiment%20is%20evident.%20%26quot%3BIs%20it%20normal%20to%20get%20zero%20training%20as%20a%20new%20manager%3F%26quot%3B%20one%20Redditor%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reddit.com%2Fr%2Fmanagers%2Fcomments%2F1d6soeu%2Fno_training_in_a_figure_it_out_situation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easked%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20reviewed%20the%20team's%20work%20over%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%2C%20asked%20them%20questions%20to%20clarify%20a%20few%20things%2C%20and%20asked%20my%20boss%20questions%20to%20clarify%20a%20few%20things%20and%20have%20basically%20picked%20up%20most%20of%20it.%20Thought%20it%20was%20kind%20weird%20I%20got%20zero%20training%2C%20though.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETechnology%20is%20supposed%20to%20make%20training%20better%2C%20in%20theory.%20Why%20have%20an%20HR%20person%20go%20over%20the%20same%20PowerPoint%20on%20vacation%20policy%20for%20every%20new%20hire%20when%20a%20quick%20video%20or%20document%20stored%20away%20somewhere%20can%20do%20it%20just%20fine%3F%20That%20may%20work%20for%20simple%20processes%20like%20requesting%20time%20off%20or%20finding%20subscription%20logins%2C%20but%20it%20can%20become%20a%20problem%20when%20companies%20try%20to%20throw%20technology%20at%20their%20more-in-depth%20training%20problems.%20Nobody%20knows%20what%20they're%20doing%20here%3F%20Why%20not%20get%20an%20app%20to%20fix%20that%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20biggest%20issues%20with%20using%20tech%20to%20solve%20what's%20ultimately%20a%20human%20problem%20is%20that%20it's%20hard%20to%20know%20if%20anyone%20is%20even%20going%20to%20use%20it.%20Take%20mentorship%3A%20Having%20one-on-one%20coaching%20from%20someone%20with%20more%20experience%20can%20help%20workers%20gain%20skills%20and%20knowledge%20that%20can't%20be%20found%20in%20a%20training%20video.%20It%20can%20also%20make%20workers%20likelier%20to%20stick%20around%20longer%2C%20help%20them%20feel%20more%20connected%2C%20and%20boost%20the%20sharing%20of%20institutional%20knowledge.%20Fostering%20these%20kinds%20of%20relationships%20is%20important%2C%20hence%20why%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mentorcliq.com%2Fblog%2Fmentoring-impact-report%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evast%20majority%20of%20Fortune%20500%20companies%20say%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20have%20mentoring%20programs%2C%20many%20of%20which%20are%20facilitated%20by%20apps%20and%20software.%20How%20many%20people%20are%20actually%20using%20those%20programs%2C%20however%2C%20is%20unclear.%20Christy%20Pettit%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20Pollinate%20Networks%2C%20which%20creates%20mentoring%20software%2C%20told%20me%20she%20recently%20spoke%20with%20a%20large%20multinational%20that%20told%20her%20despite%20having%202%2C000%20licenses%20for%20the%20mentoring%20program%2C%20which%20was%20mainly%20an%20app%2C%20fewer%20than%20200%20people%20were%20using%20it%20and%20participation%20was%20declining%20every%20quarter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMost%20companies%20say%20they%20have%20a%20mentoring%20program%2C%20but%20few%20have%20one%20that%20works%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20feels%20a%20little%20bit%20like%20when%20you%20buy%20a%20gym%20membership%2C%20and%20it%20makes%20you%20feel%20like%20you're%20doing%20something%2C%20but%20you%20may%20or%20may%20not%20be%20going%20to%20the%20gym.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20cases%2C%20tech-based%20training%20materials%20are%20disconnected%20from%20the%20realities%20of%20the%20work.%20All%20the%20training%20videos%20are%20done%20in%20an%20%26quot%3Bofficial%26quot%3B%20corporate%20speak%20it%20turns%20out%20nobody%20actually%20uses%2C%20Matos%2C%20from%20HiBob%2C%20said.%20Or%20managers%20aren't%20well%20versed%20in%20what%20their%20charges%20are%20being%20taught%20and%20end%20up%20wanting%20the%20task%20done%20differently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20when%20companies%20invest%20in%20training%2C%20it%20can%20often%20be%20directed%20toward%20the%20wrong%20people.%20Herd%20said%20that%20businesses%20often%20make%20the%20mistake%20of%20spending%20a%20ton%20of%20money%20on%20fancy%20retreats%20and%20training%20courses%20for%20their%20most%20senior%20leaders%20without%20making%20much%2C%20if%20any%2C%20investment%20in%20the%20bottom%20rungs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20could%20spend%20a%20fraction%20of%20that%20and%20give%20good%20training%20to%20all%20of%20your%20employees%2C%20and%20you're%20probably%20going%20to%20get%20more%20ROI%20if%20that's%20what%20you're%20focused%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStephanie%20Wolf%2C%20a%20vice%20president%20at%20RebuttalPR%2C%20a%20legal-communications%20firm%2C%20said%20the%20company%20learned%20the%20hard%20way%20about%20the%20costs%20of%20not%20investing%20enough%20time%20and%20energy%20in%20training%20people.%20As%20the%20firm%20grew%2C%20managers%20wouldn't%20realize%20people%20didn't%20know%20how%20to%20do%20timely%20tasks%20until%20they%20became%20urgent%2C%20or%20they'd%20discover%20employees%20were%20doing%20things%20in%20a%20way%20that%20wasn't%20consistent%20with%20the%20documentation%20and%20processes%20in%20place.%20That%20meant%20they%20had%20to%20rely%20more%20on%20senior%20staff%20to%20do%20the%20work%20and%20that%20projects%20took%20longer%20because%20training%20was%20happening%20alongside%20execution.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20seen%20how%20our%20whole%20team%20can%20suffer%20when%20we%20don't%20train%20folks%20thoroughly%20enough%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20To%20ensure%20accountability%2C%20she's%20now%20the%20point%20person%20on%20training%2C%20because%20the%20company%20found%20that%20when%20training%20was%20everyone's%20job%2C%20it%20was%20no%20one's.%20The%20firm%20has%20taken%20steps%20to%20get%20all%20the%20necessary%20information%20in%20one%20place%20and%20to%20slow%20the%20onboarding%20process%20down%20%E2%80%94%20instead%20of%20expecting%20people%20to%20take%20a%20week%20to%20get%20up%20to%20speed%2C%20it%20now%20gives%20them%20about%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWolf%20acknowledged%20it's%20%26quot%3Bsuper%20easy%20for%20training%20to%20fall%20by%20the%20wayside%20when%20your%20client%20work%20gets%20busy%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20means%20not%20allowing%20that%20to%20happen%20is%20a%20conscious%20effort.%20%26quot%3BInvesting%20time%20now%20is%20going%20to%20save%20us%20all%20time%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20easy%20to%20blame%20hybrid%20and%20remote%20work%20for%20some%20of%20these%20issues%2C%20to%20argue%20that%20if%20people%20were%20just%20gathered%20in%20an%20office%20together%2C%20that%20would%20fix%20things.%20But%20many%20HR%20professionals%20and%20career%20coaches%20say%20that's%20not%20necessarily%20the%20case.%20Yes%2C%20human%20interaction%20is%20helpful%2C%20but%20it%20doesn't%20solve%20problems%20like%20misaligned%20incentives%2C%20increasingly%20stretched%20managers%2C%20and%20a%20lack%20of%20a%20real%2C%20holistic%20plan%20for%20getting%20people%20up%20to%20speed.%20A%20remote-work%20training%20plan%20probably%20has%20to%20look%20different%20from%20an%20in-person%20one%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20impossible%20to%20craft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20a%20remote%20environment%2C%20you%2C%20as%20the%20leader%2C%20need%20to%20model%20and%20also%20hold%20the%20individual%20accountable%20for%20taking%20initiative%2C%20saying%2C%20'Hey%2C%20if%20you%20need%20something%2C%20I%20need%20you%20to%20tell%20me%20because%20I%20can't%20see%20you%2C'%26quot%3B%20Phoebe%20Gavin%2C%20a%20career%20and%20leadership%20coach%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGavin%20emphasized%20that%20it's%20not%20just%20on%20companies%20and%20managers%20to%20make%20sure%20employees%20are%20learning%20and%20getting%20onboarded%20but%20also%20on%20individual%20workers.%20Essentially%2C%20if%20you%20see%20something%20%E2%80%94%20or%20don't%20know%20something%20%E2%80%94%20say%20something.%20Ask%20questions%2C%20or%20take%20the%20initiative%20to%20figure%20things%20out%20on%20your%20own.%20I%20told%20her%20about%20an%20experience%20I'd%20had%20at%20a%20job%20where%20on%20my%20first%20day%2C%20one%20of%20four%20%26quot%3Bimportant%26quot%3B%20passwords%20I'd%20received%20was%20for%20software%20the%20company%20didn't%20use%20anymore.%20I%20expressed%20disappointment%20that%20the%20HR%20department%20hadn't%20caught%20the%20error%2C%20which%20it%20took%20me%20a%20long%20time%20to%20figure%20out%20even%20was%20an%20error.%20She%20pointed%20out%20that%20I%20should%20have%20then%20gone%20to%20HR%20to%20alert%20them%20to%20the%20error%20so%20the%20next%20new%20person%20didn't%20have%20the%20same%20experience.%20I%20did%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20tiny%20place%20where%20you%20could%20have%20a%20positive%20impact%2C%26quot%3B%20Gavin%20said.%20It%20wasn't%20necessarily%20my%20fault%2C%20she%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BJust%20that%20was%20an%20opportunity%20that%20you%20didn't%20take%2C%20and%20those%20sorts%20of%20things%20happen%20all%20the%20time.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20not%20everyone%20gets%20the%20chance%20to%20sound%20the%20alarm%20on%20their%20employer's%20faulty%20training%20system%20before%20it's%20too%20late.%20That's%20what%20happened%20to%20Michelle%2C%20which%20is%20a%20pseudonym%20I'm%20using%20to%20protect%20her%20privacy.%20Before%20starting%20a%20job%20at%20a%20science-focused%20communications%20firm%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20she%20was%20assured%20that%20she%20would%20get%20all%20the%20training%20she%20needed%20to%20overcome%20the%20fact%20that%20she%20didn't%20come%20from%20a%20scientific%20background.%20When%20she%20started%2C%20she%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20deluge%20of%20training%20modules%20and%20videos%20that%20were%20added%20to%20her%20plate%20on%20top%20of%20the%20tasks%20of%20the%20job%20itself.%20There%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20meetings%20with%20other%2C%20more%20seasoned%20coworkers%20after%20those%20video%20training%20sessions%2C%20but%20eventually%2C%20almost%20everyone%20stopped%20showing%20up.%20She%20was%20fired%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20weeks%20after%20being%20told%20she%20wasn't%20picking%20things%20up%20fast%20enough.%20She%20said%20she%20received%20little%20feedback%20and%20hadn't%20been%20given%20warning%20that%20things%20were%20going%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20felt%20blindsided%20by%20the%20termination%20just%20because%20I%20didn't%20think%20I%20was%20given%20enough%20time%20to%20do%20all%20of%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20led%20to%20believe%20they%20would%20kind%20of%20hold%20my%20hand%20a%20little%20bit%20at%20the%20beginning%2C%20and%20a%20month%20in%2C%20to%20me%2C%20is%20very%20much%20still%20the%20beginning.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20know%20how%20there%20are%20certain%20tasks%20in%20life%20that%20feel%20designed%20to%20be%20so%20complex%20that%20you'll%20give%20up%3F%20Like%20filing%20an%20insurance%20claim%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcancel-subscriptions-congress-ftc-dark-practices-autorenewal-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equitting%20the%20gym%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Work%20should%20not%20be%20like%20that%2C%20but%20for%20many%20people%2C%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployees%20have%20complained%20about%20just%20being%20thrown%20into%20the%20fire%20forever.%20Many%20employers%20subscribe%20to%20the%20idea%20that%20you%20just%20toss%20people%20into%20the%20water%20and%20see%20who%20can%20swim.%20Trial%20by%20error%20is%20part%20of%20learning%20at%20work%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20best%20ways%20to%20learn%20how%20to%20do%20something%20is%20to%20just%20try%20doing%20it.%20But%20it%20shouldn't%20be%20the%20entire%20approach.%20You%20know%20how%20you%20learn%20at%20school%3F%20The%20teacher%20explains%20something%2C%20you%20do%20your%20homework%2C%20it%20gets%20graded%2C%20you%20take%20a%20test%2C%20and%20you%20move%20on%20once%20you%20more%20or%20less%20figure%20it%20out.%20Imagine%20if%20teachers%20just%20piled%2015%20algebra%20tests%20on%20high-school%20students%20and%20everyone%20hoped%20for%20the%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20aspects%20of%20the%20current%20workplace%20environment%20that%20make%20training%20more%20complicated%20to%20tackle.%20Remote%20work%20is%20different%20%E2%80%94%20you%20can't%20just%20lean%20over%20and%20ask%20the%20person%20next%20to%20you%20how%20this%20one%20software%20works%20again%20when%20you're%20typing%20on%20your%20laptop%20alone%20from%20your%20couch.%20Workers%20and%20employers%20don't%20feel%20as%20tied%20to%20one%20another%2C%20so%20there%20may%20be%20a%20decline%20in%20investment%20from%20both%20sides%20in%20the%20idea%20of%20getting%20%3Cem%3Esupergood%3C%2Fem%3E%20at%20the%20task%20at%20hand.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fremote-workers-middle-managers-most-affected-by-layoffs-experts-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emiddle-management%20class%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20increasingly%20stretched%20thin%20and%20hollowed%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbove%20all%2C%20it's%20really%20easy%20to%20load%20up%20on%20a%20bunch%20of%20tech-based%20solutions%20without%20identifying%20whether%20they%20actually%20solve%20anything.%20Relying%20on%20tech%20is%20appealing%20financially%20because%20buying%20a%20software%20license%20is%20a%20heck%20of%20a%20lot%20cheaper%20than%20paying%20a%20real%20live%20person.%20Many%20of%20the%20HR%20experts%20I%20talked%20to%20for%20this%20story%20suggested%20the%20training%20gap%20was%20a%20problem%20artificial%20intelligence%20might%20fix%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgenerative-ai-exaggeration-openai-nvidia-microsoft-chatgpt-jobs-investors-markets-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommon%20refrain%20for%20intractable%20problems%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20no%20matter%20the%20industry.%20Maybe%20that's%20true%20%E2%80%94%20if%20your%20manager%20won't%20have%20a%20one-on-one%20with%20you%2C%20having%20a%20chatbot%20to%20ask%20questions%20to%20isn't%20the%20worst%20thing%20in%20the%20world%20(assuming%20said%20chatbot%20knows%20stuff%20and%20doesn't%20make%20things%20up).%20But%20AI%20isn't%20going%20to%20be%20a%20panacea%20here.%20When%20you%20need%20to%20speak%20to%20a%20real%