els%20in%20France%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20to%20dance%20school%2C%20but%20my%20parents%20wouldn't%20let%20me.%20I%20didn't%20feel%20at%20home%20in%20France%2C%20so%20I%20went%20to%20England%20to%20learn%20English%20as%20an%20au%20pair.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20went%20on%20to%20get%20my%20bachelor's%20degree%20and%20then%20my%20master's%20in%20education%20and%20eventually%20built%20my%20life%20in%20the%20UK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeing%20adopted%20has%20massively%20impacted%20my%20career.%20I've%20had%20to%20learn%20over%20time%20to%20separate%20my%20work%20habits%20from%20my%20childhood%20experiences%20and%20learned%20behavior.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2236859d2f-0eb1-4f87-afa0-9e657cf899a9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETrying%20to%20find%20a%20sense%20of%20belonging%20at%20work%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20never%20felt%20I%20belonged%20anywhere%20or%20with%20anyone.%20To%20protect%20myself%2C%20I%20learned%20to%20move%20on%20quickly%2C%20and%20this%20pattern%20has%20seeped%20into%20my%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20stayed%20at%20my%20first%20job%20out%20of%20university%20for%20nine%20years.%20I%20worked%20at%20a%20research%20council%2C%20helping%20international%20university%20students%20with%20funding.%20I%20stuck%20it%20out%20for%20so%20long%20because%20I%20was%20afraid%20to%20push%20myself.%20I%20never%20felt%20I%20belonged%20there%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20to%20help%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20urge%20to%20belong%20dates%20back%20to%20my%20adoption.%20I%20never%20felt%20I%20belonged%20in%20a%20white%2C%20middle-class%20family%20and%20wanted%20to%20find%20it%20elsewhere.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20made%20redundant%2C%20and%20this%20pushed%20me%20to%20explore%20career%20options.%20I%20worked%20in%20makeup%20artistry%2C%20university%20administration%2C%20fashion%20editorial%2C%20community%20engagement%2C%20creative%20engagement%2C%20and%20coaching.%20I've%20been%20employed%20and%20self-employed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20impacted%20my%20career%20stability.%20If%20I%20had%20planted%20myself%2C%20I%20think%20I%20would%20have%20eventually%20found%20that%20belonging%2C%20but%20I%20never%20gave%20it%20enough%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20times%2C%20I%20feel%20like%20my%20constant%20career%20changes%20have%20held%20me%20back.%20Most%20of%20my%20peers%20who've%20stayed%20in%20one%20industry%20are%20directors%20or%20CEOs.%20However%2C%20I'm%20grateful%20for%20how%20well-rounded%20I%20am.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20I%20work%20as%20a%20coach%2C%20podcaster%2C%20artist%2C%20and%20consultant.%20I%20run%20retreats%20and%20work%20with%20arts%20and%20culture%20organizations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2270c99f44-e440-4761-b91b-b7bc500a8154%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI'd%20never%20advocate%20for%20myself%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20my%20adult%20life%2C%20I%20avoided%20putting%20myself%20forward%20for%20promotions%20or%20opportunities%20to%20advance%20my%20career.%20I%20didn't%20believe%20in%20my%20abilities%2C%20even%20if%20I%20was%20well-qualified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20there%20was%20a%20job%20opening%20while%20working%20the%20University%20of%20the%20Arts%20London%20I%20could've%20applied%20for.%20I%20had%20the%20required%20qualifications%2C%20but%20I%20didn't%20apply.%20A%20colleague%20who%20was%20far%20less%20experienced%20than%20I%20was%20applied%20for%20it%20and%20got%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESelf-worth%20is%20fostered%20as%20a%20child%20when%20people%20affirm%20us.%20When%20I%20was%20growing%20up%2C%20I%20never%20felt%20validated.%20No%20one%20%E2%80%94%20not%20the%20missionary%2C%20the%20orphanage%20staff%2C%20or%20my%20adoptive%20parents%20%E2%80%94%20felt%20like%20they%20were%20in%20my%20corner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20time%20my%20capabilities%20have%20been%20questioned%2C%20I%20retreat%20rather%20than%20push%20through%20because%20I%20didn't%20learn%20to%20believe%20in%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%2C%20when%20working%20with%20community%20engagement%20in%202021%2C%20I%20made%20a%20short%20film.%20I%20gave%20t